---
import Base from "../../layouts/Base.astro";
import Lead from "../../components/Lead.astro";
import NextSteps from "../../components/NextSteps.astro";
import { url } from "../../lib/url";
---

<Base
  title="Change is possible, slowly"
  description="Step five: nervous system patterns can change — gradually, with small and regular practice — and here's where to go next."
  crumbs={[
    { label: "home", href: "" },
    { label: "start here", href: "start/" },
  ]}
>
  <h1 class="text-3xl sm:text-4xl">Change is possible — slowly.</h1>
  <Lead>
    A stuck pattern isn't permanent. Nervous systems are shaped by repetition,
    which means they can be re-shaped by repetition too — gently, in small
    doses, over time. Not in a weekend. But genuinely, and often more than
    people expect.
  </Lead>

  <div class="prose">
    <p>
      The word that matters here is <strong>slow</strong>. This work rewards
      small and regular far more than big and forceful — in fact, pushing too
      hard tends to backfire, because a system can't feel safe while it's
      being strained. "Less is more, and slower is better" is close to a
      motto in this world. With a nervous system, slower usually <em>is</em>
      the fast way.
    </p>
    <p>
      You don't have to figure it all out today. You've already done the first
      thing that matters — you've started paying attention. From here, you
      might try a short practice, read a little more, or, when you're ready,
      look into working with a person.
    </p>
  </div>

  <NextSteps>
    <li>
      <a href={url("practices/")}>Try a short practice</a> — two to five
      minutes, matched to how you're arriving
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href={url("learn/capacity-and-the-window-of-tolerance/")}
        >Read about capacity</a
      > — why slow works, and what "widening the window" means
    </li>
    <li>
      <a href={url("modalities/")}>Look into deeper support</a> — an honest
      guide to therapies and how to find practitioners
    </li>
  </NextSteps>
</Base>
